<item>
            <title>[FELIX-4326] Possible Invalid BundleContext exception when shutting down the extender</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4326</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Due to concurrency, the extender can receive bundle events raised by the framework after the extender has been stopped.&lt;br/&gt;
The reason is that the framework internal event listener lists can be obtained before the extender is stopped, but iterated and called after the extender is stopped.&lt;br/&gt;
We need to guard against that.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
